                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cærdæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>cærdæg</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>проворный</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>brisk</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>быстрый</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>quick</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ловкий</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>nimble</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>aztæ jyl bīræ cæwy, fælæ nyrma cærdæg ū</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лет ему много, но пока еще он живой (бодрый)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>he is many years old, but he is still alive (brisk)</q></abv:tr></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Собственно „живой“, прош. причастие от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæryn"/> ‘жить’ + суффикс -%iæg%i. Ср. по образованию <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘мелкий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘чистый’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cadæg"/> ‘тихий’ и др. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čālāk</w> <gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>проворный</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is in fact “alive”, a past participle form of the verb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæryn"/> ‘live’ + suffix -%iæg%i. Cf. by the composition <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘small’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘clean’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cadæg"/> ‘quiet’ etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čālāk</w> <gloss><q>nimble</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>brisk</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>